{
  "texts": [
    "• Markov Condition every variable X in G is conditionally independent of its non- descendants given its parents.",
    "This is equivalent to saying that every conditional independence implied by d-separation in the DAG is present in the joint probability distribution P(X).",
    "Importantly, this condition means that the joint probability distri- bution P(X) can be decomposed as follows (where Pa X i are the parents of X i):",
    "• Minimality Condition we cannot remove any of the edges in the DAG without the graph implying a conditional independence relationship that is not present in P(X).",
    "Pearl (1988) expresses these two conditions by saying that G is a minimal Independ- ence-Map (I-map) of P(X)."
  ]
}